r_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "### issue\r\nSpecified that the std::io::[copy](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/io/fn.copy.html) function should copy the data. But the data is not copied and transferred.\r\n\r\n### Code\r\n```rust\r\n// std::io::copy \r\nuse std::io;\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let mut reader: &[u8] = b\"hello\";\r\n    let mut writer: Vec<u8> = vec![];\r\n\r\n    io::copy(&mut reader, &mut writer).unwrap();\r\n\r\n    println!(\"reader: {:?}\", &reader); // reader: []\r\n    println!(\"writer: {:?}\", &writer); // writer: [104, 101, 108, 108, 111]\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Meta\r\n`rustc --version --verbose`:\r\n\r\n```\r\nrustc 1.59.0 (9d1b2106e 2022-02-23)\r\nbinary: rustc\r\ncommit-hash: 9d1b2106e23b1abd32fce1f17267604a5102f57a\r\ncommit-date: 2022-02-23\r\nhost: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\nrelease: 1.59.0\r\nLLVM version: 13.0.0\r\n```", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/95756/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/95756/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}